9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
10 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 2 O.S. 2021, Section 6-313, is
11 amended to read as follows:
12 Section 6-313. A. All catfish, minnows, fingerlings, fish,
13 frogs, and other aquatic species which are legally produced,
14 pursuant to the provisions of this act, shall be confined to the
15 lands and waters of the licensee in such a manner so as to prohibit:
16 1. Contact with wild fish or other aquatic species in public
17 waters; and
18 2. Such wild fish or other aquatic species in from being
19 commercially harvested from public waters from and becoming a part
20 of the commercial production sold as a wild-born commodity. As used
21 in this paragraph, “wild-born” means wild fish or aquatic species
22 born in public waters and not introduced though aquaculture.
23 B. 1. Except as otherwise provided by this subsection, the
24 Oklahoma Department of Agriculture, Food, and Forestry shall not
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB777 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)
1 rest rict the manner in which persons, licensed pursuant to this act,
2 gather or impound aquatic species raised within the impoundments in
3 their commercial operations.
4 2. No person shall sell or attempt to sell game fish and/or
5 paddlefish obtained from public waters that have been commingled
6 with privately produced fish subject to the provisions of this act
7 capture wild fish or aquatic species for direct sale. Licensed
8 producers may harvest both game fish and nongame fish from public
9 waters for use in aquaculture; provided, that the licensed producer
10 complies with all applicable regulations set forth by the Department
11 of Wildlife Conservation.
12 C. No licensee may receive, free of charge, any catfish,
13 minnow, fingerling, fish, frog or other aquatic species from the
14 state or federal government.
15 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 29 O.S. 2021, Section 2-115, is
16 amended to read as follows:
17 Section 2-115. “Game fish” is a fish normally sought after by
18 sportsmen, and includes only largemouth bass, smallmouth bass, white
19 bass, spotted bass, black crappie, white crappie, northern pike,
20 trout, sauger, saugeye, striped bass, hybrid striped bass, walleye,
21 paddlefish, blue catfish and channel catfish. Blue catfish and
22 channel catfish are herein defined to mean “forked tail” catfish.
23 SECTION 3. REPEALER 29 O.S. 2021, Section 6-303.1, is
24 hereby repealed.
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB777 SFLR Page 2
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)
1 SECTION 4. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
2 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON AGRICULTURE AND WILDLIFE
